  <title translate="true">Groundwater Transport</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">Groundwater Transport</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Transport of solutes through the groundwater can be simulated with MT3DMS, MT3D-USGS, or the Groundwater Transport (GWT) Process of MODFLOW 6. The chemical species used for transport with all three programs are specified on the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Chem-Species-(MT3D-and-GWT)" styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Chem Species (MT3D and GWT)</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> pane. Some data sets, such as porosity, are also shared between MT3D and GWT. Data for GWT are specified under </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="GWT-Groundwater-Transport" styleclass="Strong" translate="true">GWT: Groundwater Transport</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> and for MT3D under </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MT3DMS" styleclass="Strong" translate="true">MT3DMS or MT3D-USGS</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">.</text></para>
  </body>
